Class LegacyInstallation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gbif.api.model.registry.Installation
      • org.gbif.registry.ws.model.LegacyInstallation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.gbif.api.model.registry.Commentable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Contactable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Endpointable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Identifiable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.LenientEquals<org.gbif.api.model.registry.Installation>, org.gbif.api.model.registry.MachineTaggable, org.gbif.api.model.registry.NetworkEntity, org.gbif.api.model.registry.Taggable

    public class LegacyInstallation
extends org.gbif.api.model.registry.Installation
    Class used to create or update an Installation for legacy (GBRDS/IPT) API. A set of HTTP Form parameters coming from a POST request are injected.
    Its fields are injected using the @FormParam. It is assumed the following parameters exist in the HTTP request: 'organisationKey', 'name', 'description', 'primaryContactName', 'primaryContactEmail', 'primaryContactType', 'serviceTypes', 'serviceURLs', and 'wsPassword'.
    JAXB annotations allow the class to be converted into an XML document, that gets included in the Response following a successful registration or update. @XmlElement is used to specify element names that consumers of legacy services expect to find.

        Set the title.
        The title must be at least 2 characters long, a limit set in the database schema. Since older versions of the IPT may not have imposed the same limit, the field is padded if necessary so as to avoid problems during persistence.
